The article is a statement from the White House Office of the Press Secretary regarding the UN Security Council Presidential Statement on the Cheonan incident. The statement condemns North Korea's attack on the Cheonan and warns them that such aggressive behavior will not be tolerated by the international community. The statement reflects the shared view of the 5 members of the Six-Party Talks and endorses the findings of the Joint Investigative Group that established North Korea's responsibility for the attack. The Republic of Korea's restraint in response to North Korean belligerence is commended, and the US reiterates its commitment to the defense of South Korea. The statement also highlights the increasing international isolation of North Korea and the strong sanctions it faces through UNSC Resolution 1874, as the international community continues to show the cost of North Korea's provocative behavior.